In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 17, 2014, as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23, 2014, as Constitution Week. The proclamation highlights the significance of the Constitution in shaping the principles and values of the United States. It acknowledges the contributions of immigrants to the nation and emphasizes the importance of active citizenship and participation in upholding the rights and responsibilities outlined in the Constitution. The President encourages officials and community leaders to organize ceremonies and programs that reflect on the importance of citizenship and the enduring strength of the Constitution.